WEBVTT

00:06.267 --> 00:09.270
Sam, I don't want to leave.
Now I know how to take
care of my problems.

00:09.400 --> 00:11.228
I guess I'm gonna
have to take on Tammy.

00:11.359 --> 00:13.056
We have a chance of
figuring this out together.

00:13.187 --> 00:15.363
Or I can start
getting answers on my own.

00:15.667 --> 00:16.755
No one listens to me.

00:16.886 --> 00:18.757
I've never been a problem
for you.

00:18.888 --> 00:20.107
I took care of my little

00:20.237 --> 00:22.413
Tammy's gonna arrest me
for arson problem.

00:22.544 --> 00:25.982
All you have to do
is sign this affidavit.

00:26.113 --> 00:27.462
She knows.
I'm so sorry.

00:27.592 --> 00:28.419
I'll fix it.

00:28.550 --> 00:29.768
This is Allison's.

00:29.899 --> 00:30.987
We think there's been
an accident.

00:31.118 --> 00:32.554
Where is she?
I don't know.

00:32.683 --> 00:35.426
♪

00:36.688 --> 00:38.342
[Indistinct conversations]

00:38.473 --> 00:46.524
♪

00:47.743 --> 00:49.136
What?

00:49.266 --> 00:51.442
♪

00:51.573 --> 00:53.836
Can I get you
another tea?

00:53.966 --> 00:57.405
Uh, I'd love one.
Thank you.

00:57.535 --> 00:58.841
Patron: Allison.

01:02.932 --> 01:06.109
Actually, I'm okay.
Thanks.

01:13.073 --> 01:17.468
♪

01:17.599 --> 01:20.036
Kevin, you have to
start doing dishes.

01:20.167 --> 01:22.256
I tried that one time.

01:22.386 --> 01:25.259
No, you licked all the dishes
and put them back.

01:25.389 --> 01:27.609
Pete, what do you think
"licked it clean" means?

01:27.739 --> 01:29.045
[ Laughter ]

01:29.176 --> 01:32.134
I guess I'm...
just bad at it

01:32.265 --> 01:35.616
because dishes...
remind me of Allison.

01:35.747 --> 01:38.663
[ Laughter ]

01:38.794 --> 01:41.231
Sometimes I wonder
if I'll ever recover

01:41.362 --> 01:43.190
from her
untimely passing.

01:43.320 --> 01:44.452
Hey, hon.

01:44.582 --> 01:47.324
Oh, hey, babe!

01:47.455 --> 01:48.412
You were saying?

01:48.543 --> 01:49.761
I don't know.
Was I talking?

01:49.892 --> 01:51.545
Hey, Molly.Hello, boys.

01:51.676 --> 01:53.896
Oh, you brought
my Miller Lite!
Yeah.

01:54.026 --> 01:55.376
How much do I owe ya?

01:55.506 --> 01:56.899
Oh, my treat.

01:57.029 --> 01:59.467
Also, I'm cooking later
for the big game.

01:59.597 --> 02:00.685
You're hear a lot, Molly.

02:00.816 --> 02:02.165
Yeah, well,
Kevin needs me.

02:02.296 --> 02:04.515
You know, like that time
he got his arm stuck

02:04.646 --> 02:06.691
in the refrigerator.

02:06.822 --> 02:09.912
It's true.
I might've died of starvation.

02:11.174 --> 02:12.784
Which is ironic.

02:12.915 --> 02:14.786
Alanis Morissette
taught me that.

02:14.917 --> 02:16.048
[Patting]

02:16.179 --> 02:18.790
So Kevin would've died
without you?

02:18.921 --> 02:20.662
Maybe you should
go home sometimes.

02:20.792 --> 02:24.274
[Laughs]

02:24.405 --> 02:27.582
Ahh...

02:27.712 --> 02:30.106
No, no, she --
she shouldn't go home, Neil,

02:30.237 --> 02:32.108
because she's
my girlfriend.

02:32.239 --> 02:34.545
Like, you know how you feel
about curly fries?

02:34.676 --> 02:39.376
Imagine if another human being
felt that way about you.

02:39.507 --> 02:41.683
That's what we have.Aww.

02:41.813 --> 02:44.512
I like having
Molly here.

02:44.642 --> 02:46.427
You made everything
so much better.

02:46.557 --> 02:49.821
Y-You've given me, us, our lives
back these last six months.

02:49.952 --> 02:51.432
Well, that's nice, Neil.

02:51.562 --> 02:54.216
Uh, but Kevin and I have
only been together for four.

02:54.348 --> 02:56.393
Yeah, Allison's
been gone six months.

02:56.524 --> 02:59.788
Huh. Well, I'd say,
"Ding-dong, the witch is dead,"

02:59.918 --> 03:01.529
but that would be
insensitive.

03:01.659 --> 03:03.879
So I won't say it.
Adiós.

03:06.621 --> 03:08.318
Yeah.

03:08.449 --> 03:14.629
♪

03:14.759 --> 03:16.326
[Breathes deeply]

03:16.457 --> 03:20.200
♪

03:20.329 --> 03:23.942
Yeah.
What do you think?

03:24.073 --> 03:25.727
I think it's rearranging
deck chairs

03:25.857 --> 03:28.120
on the Titanic
at this point.

03:28.251 --> 03:29.992
But it's nice.

03:30.122 --> 03:31.689
Gonna be $85, Judi.

03:31.820 --> 03:33.343
Okay.

03:36.912 --> 03:38.914
Okay.
Thank you.

03:39.043 --> 03:42.352
Oh. And here.

03:42.483 --> 03:44.485
Oh.

03:44.615 --> 03:45.834
Small print.

03:45.964 --> 03:48.619
Oh, stop that.
You'll like it.

03:48.750 --> 03:49.793
You been reading much?

03:49.925 --> 03:52.971
Yeah. Sometimes.

03:53.102 --> 03:54.582
I've been busy.

03:54.712 --> 03:56.018
That's stupid.

03:56.148 --> 03:58.673
I don't care what
you have going on, okay?

03:58.803 --> 04:00.152
Or who you live with.

04:00.283 --> 04:02.764
You don't forget
who you are.

04:02.894 --> 04:04.548
Okay.

04:04.679 --> 04:07.203
Mm!

04:10.119 --> 04:13.383
[Door opens, bell jingles]

04:13.514 --> 04:15.429
[Door closes]

04:15.559 --> 04:23.567
♪

04:24.133 --> 04:32.183
♪

04:32.707 --> 04:40.758
♪

04:41.585 --> 04:43.021
Yeah, hi. Uh...

04:43.152 --> 04:45.633
I'm looking for a number
in New Brunswick County.

04:48.592 --> 04:50.072
Gertrude Fronch?

04:51.813 --> 04:54.294
[Thunder rumbling]

04:54.424 --> 04:56.470
[ Laughter ]

04:56.600 --> 04:59.081
[High-pitched ringing]

05:00.952 --> 05:02.998
[Birds chirping]

05:05.174 --> 05:13.225
♪

05:14.618 --> 05:15.837
[Grunts]

05:15.967 --> 05:23.627
♪

05:23.758 --> 05:31.679
♪

05:31.809 --> 05:33.289
[Lock clicks]

05:33.420 --> 05:36.510
♪

05:39.643 --> 05:41.123
[Keys jingling]

05:46.520 --> 05:49.566
♪

05:49.697 --> 05:52.700
Hey, Dad! Can you come
in here real quick?!

05:52.830 --> 05:55.093
And, uh,
bring some pancakes!

05:55.224 --> 05:57.052
[ Laughter ]

05:58.662 --> 06:01.535
Oh. Oh, boy.
This is tough.

06:01.665 --> 06:04.364
But I knew
this day would come.

06:04.494 --> 06:08.803
Buddy, I said "pancakes,"
not "suitcase."

06:08.933 --> 06:10.239
[ Laughter ]

06:10.370 --> 06:11.936
Kevin,
it's time I leave.

06:12.067 --> 06:13.982
I've been sticking around
'cause you're in mourning,

06:14.112 --> 06:16.419
but it's starting to feel
like you're taking advantage.

06:16.550 --> 06:18.203
I don't know what
you're talking about.

06:18.334 --> 06:20.031
This morning,
you made me tie your shoes

06:20.162 --> 06:22.512
'cause it reminded you
of Allison.

06:22.643 --> 06:26.081
I do bunny ears, and
she loved Easter so much.

06:27.604 --> 06:29.345
I guess you just forgt
about all that

06:29.476 --> 06:33.828
because of your
just-on-time-set Alzheimer's.

06:33.957 --> 06:36.918
I do not have --

06:37.048 --> 06:39.007
Look, Kevin, Lorraine has
a condo down in Florida.

06:39.137 --> 06:41.009
We're gonna be going there
for the winter.

06:41.139 --> 06:44.491
-It's summer.
-And all the other seasons.

06:44.621 --> 06:48.277
Fine! Go follow that
old crone down to Florida!

06:48.408 --> 06:51.454
I'll see you for three weeks
in February to work on my tan!

06:51.585 --> 06:54.152
You think I'm gonna
tell you the address?

06:54.283 --> 06:55.545
Come on.

07:00.811 --> 07:02.117
Oop. Okay.

07:03.292 --> 07:05.381
[Groans]

07:05.512 --> 07:08.515
Why don't you sit down
and I will just serve you?

07:08.645 --> 07:11.169
Mm! If you insist.

07:11.300 --> 07:16.044
♪

07:16.174 --> 07:18.176
We need
a bigger place.

07:18.307 --> 07:19.439
What?

07:19.569 --> 07:20.875
Four people lived
in this apartment

07:21.005 --> 07:23.399
for the first 11 years
of my life.

07:23.530 --> 07:26.184
Plus, my Uncle Tim
when he first got out of jail.

07:26.315 --> 07:28.535
Oh, yeah, I can see why
you're dying to stay here.

07:28.665 --> 07:32.234
Hate to leave all those great
Worcester memories behind.

07:33.714 --> 07:36.064
Tammy.

07:36.194 --> 07:38.719
Would a new place
be so bad?

07:38.849 --> 07:43.637
Especially after everything
that happened with Allison?

07:43.767 --> 07:47.162
♪

07:47.292 --> 07:50.078
I know I shouldn't
have helped her.

07:50.207 --> 07:53.690
But she needed the pills.
And it got Nick off her back.

07:53.821 --> 07:56.258
I know, I know. I don't need
to go through it again.

07:56.388 --> 07:57.999
I know why you wanted me
to move in here.

07:58.129 --> 08:00.131
It would have been a lot
of change all at once.

08:00.262 --> 08:02.264
But it's been,
like, six months,

08:02.394 --> 08:06.355
and I feel like
we're...stuck.

08:07.922 --> 08:10.185
Don't you?

08:10.315 --> 08:12.840
I don't know.

08:12.970 --> 08:14.624
Maybe.

08:14.755 --> 08:21.109
♪

08:21.239 --> 08:23.285
What's really
keeping us here?

08:25.243 --> 08:27.637
My business.
Your job.

08:27.768 --> 08:29.421
You can cut hair
from anywhere.

08:29.552 --> 08:32.294
And my job -- [Scoffs]
I just watched another

08:32.424 --> 08:34.688
Patrick O'Irishwhatever
make detective

08:34.818 --> 08:38.342
after two years
on the job.

08:38.474 --> 08:41.433
And in another two years,
he'll probably be my boss.

08:41.563 --> 08:43.697
I'm fine with
leaving Worcester.

08:43.827 --> 08:47.875
♪

08:48.005 --> 08:50.660
This is the only place
I've ever lived.

08:50.790 --> 08:53.402
♪

08:53.533 --> 08:55.535
Look, Patty.

08:55.665 --> 08:58.842
This is the only place
you've ever lived.

08:58.973 --> 09:03.847
♪

09:03.978 --> 09:08.939
♪

09:09.070 --> 09:10.114
Hey, you settle
the register?

09:10.245 --> 09:13.117
-Yep. Even.
-Ah. Nice work.

09:13.248 --> 09:14.728
Pam would've liked you.

09:14.858 --> 09:16.120
Pam, as in...?

09:16.251 --> 09:18.122
Oh. From the name.

09:21.865 --> 09:23.301
I didn't know she was real.
[Chuckles]

09:23.432 --> 09:26.522
I know I only brought you on
for the summer, but...

09:26.653 --> 09:27.958
how'd you like to stay?

09:28.089 --> 09:30.091
I-I feel like
you belong here.

09:30.221 --> 09:32.006
Yeah?
Yeah.

09:32.136 --> 09:34.530
You caught on really quick,
and it's only been a few weeks,

09:34.661 --> 09:36.314
and you're
practically a pro.

09:36.445 --> 09:39.187
Well, technically, I am.
You pay me.

09:39.317 --> 09:42.756
[Chuckles] Right.
And you're funny, too.

09:42.886 --> 09:44.845
You don't think someone
named Gertrude would be funny,

09:44.975 --> 09:46.498
but you are.

09:46.629 --> 09:49.327
Well, yep.
[Chuckles]

09:49.458 --> 09:51.373
Think about it.
Okay.

09:57.597 --> 10:05.126
♪

10:05.256 --> 10:13.134
♪

10:13.264 --> 10:20.794
♪

10:20.924 --> 10:23.274
Neil, best buddy, you are
not gonna believe this!

10:23.405 --> 10:24.841
My dad w--

10:24.972 --> 10:27.148
[ Laughter ]

10:27.278 --> 10:29.803
W-W--
Uh...

10:29.933 --> 10:31.500
[Laughing] Whoa!

10:31.631 --> 10:33.154
Uh, uh...no.

10:33.284 --> 10:36.157
No. No, no, man. No.
She -- She fell on top of me!

10:36.287 --> 10:38.725
Uh, uh,
she needed my gum.

10:38.855 --> 10:40.596
I'm dreaming?

10:40.727 --> 10:43.947
I could argue that I am
the one slumming it here.

10:44.078 --> 10:45.427
[Laughing]

10:45.557 --> 10:47.908
But, no, Diane. I --

10:48.038 --> 10:50.998
[Laughing]

10:52.782 --> 10:55.393
[Laughter slowing]

10:55.524 --> 10:58.222
Whew.

10:58.353 --> 11:00.529
[Laughter resumes]

11:04.576 --> 11:06.796
[Laughter continues]

11:10.931 --> 11:13.194
[ Laughter ]

11:13.324 --> 11:15.936
♪

11:19.504 --> 11:21.550
[Indistinct conversations]

11:26.947 --> 11:29.036
Sorry. I got caught up
with some stuff.

11:29.166 --> 11:31.516
Mm. That's fine.

11:31.647 --> 11:35.216
I ordered
a bacon egg-n-cheese.

11:35.346 --> 11:36.652
Yeah.

11:36.783 --> 11:40.003
♪

11:40.134 --> 11:42.397
Oh. Okay.

11:44.094 --> 11:45.966
Anything new?

11:46.096 --> 11:47.228
So, I'm pretty sure she ws
working at a Dollar Store

11:47.358 --> 11:49.578
in Vermont
a few weeks ago.

11:49.709 --> 11:51.711
Vermont.

11:51.841 --> 11:53.582
She might be moving south.

11:55.758 --> 11:57.891
You look tired.

11:58.021 --> 12:00.502
Are you an actual idiot?
Saying that to a woman?

12:00.632 --> 12:03.287
Probably.
Um, I'm still gonna ask.

12:03.418 --> 12:06.508
Uh, are you okay?

12:06.638 --> 12:09.467
Are you sleeping?

12:09.598 --> 12:12.514
I just want to make sure
she's alright.

12:12.644 --> 12:16.039
I think about her.
Don't you?

12:16.170 --> 12:17.258
No.

12:17.388 --> 12:20.174
Liar.
I don't.

12:20.304 --> 12:23.351
She left on her own, and I don't
think she wants to be found.

12:23.481 --> 12:26.049
Yes, she does.
She's Allison.

12:26.180 --> 12:29.009
Yeah, and I know
Allie, too, and --
Oh, no.

12:29.139 --> 12:32.055
Because you still call her that
like she's 17? Jesus.

12:32.186 --> 12:34.318
Well, yeah, she's still
the same person, right?

12:34.449 --> 12:36.103
I mean,
people don't change.

12:38.670 --> 12:43.066
But sh--
she actually...did.

12:43.197 --> 12:46.069
♪

12:46.200 --> 12:47.941
I don't even think
she realized it.

12:50.204 --> 12:53.773
She gave up everything
to protect me.

12:53.903 --> 12:55.513
And now that I'm left here
without her,

12:55.644 --> 12:56.993
I don't feel better off.

12:57.124 --> 13:00.518
I just feel...left.

13:00.649 --> 13:05.741
♪

13:05.872 --> 13:10.877
♪

13:11.007 --> 13:13.793
I think the most fun I ever had
was sitting on my couch

13:13.923 --> 13:17.318
next to her trying
to pull her teeth out.

13:17.448 --> 13:19.189
What?

13:20.887 --> 13:23.237
Well.

13:23.367 --> 13:24.804
It's complicated.

13:24.934 --> 13:28.938
Yeah, well, Allison's
a complicated person.

13:30.897 --> 13:33.203
She's my favorite person.

13:34.683 --> 13:37.425
And she did this because she
thought it would fix everything,

13:37.555 --> 13:39.688
not because she wanted to.

13:39.819 --> 13:41.777
She wants to be found.

13:41.908 --> 13:42.996
♪

13:43.126 --> 13:45.999
Then why is she
so good at running?

13:46.129 --> 13:50.307
♪

13:52.396 --> 13:53.397
Here you go.

13:53.528 --> 13:55.443
Another one?Yep. [Chuckles]

13:55.573 --> 13:58.402
I guess, uh, Doris Lyman
spent half her life

13:58.533 --> 13:59.969
at Eileen Fisher's.

14:00.100 --> 14:03.407
[Chuckles]
Lucky us.

14:03.538 --> 14:06.584
These are pretty!

14:06.715 --> 14:08.760
Sure.[Door closes]

14:08.891 --> 14:11.241
Hey, you said your brother
was a handyman, right?

14:11.372 --> 14:13.243
Hmm. Michael.
The golden boy.

14:13.374 --> 14:15.593
Right.
Do you think he could, uh,

14:15.724 --> 14:17.595
come by my apartment
to fix my window?

14:17.726 --> 14:19.597
It's been like two weeks,
and I can't get it shut.

14:19.728 --> 14:21.817
I'll ask him, but he's
too busy to come to mine.

14:21.948 --> 14:23.775
At least
your garbage disposal

14:23.906 --> 14:26.169
isn't backing up
into your bathtub.

14:26.300 --> 14:28.215
Be grateful.

14:28.345 --> 14:30.043
Mm. Gratitude.

14:30.173 --> 14:32.436
Mm!
Right.

14:32.567 --> 14:36.658
Whew! I swear, all these bags
smell like Chanel No. 5.

14:36.788 --> 14:38.790
I know. These are
some fancy ladies.

14:38.921 --> 14:42.664
Yeah.
Fancy dead ladies.

14:42.794 --> 14:45.058
That's...kinda dark.
[Chuckles]

14:45.188 --> 14:49.062
♪

14:49.192 --> 14:50.324
Hm.

14:50.454 --> 14:52.195
[Chuckles]

14:52.326 --> 14:53.631
[Laughter]

14:53.762 --> 14:56.417
Oh, hey.Ah, well, well!

14:56.547 --> 14:59.507
If it isn't my supposed
best friend,

14:59.637 --> 15:01.248
here in the bar
of mine enemies.

15:01.378 --> 15:03.511
You can add that
to the list of things

15:03.641 --> 15:05.687
I'll be expecting
an apology for tonight!

15:05.817 --> 15:07.297
We came here
to get an apology?

15:07.428 --> 15:08.864
I thought
this was date night.

15:08.995 --> 15:11.432
Um, explain to me
why you deserve the apology.

15:11.562 --> 15:12.694
Because you've been lying

15:12.824 --> 15:15.088
and ditching me
to star in your very own

15:15.218 --> 15:18.526
Barnum & Bailey sideshow
with that grandma!

15:18.656 --> 15:20.702
Diane is not a grandma!

15:20.832 --> 15:22.486
But, I mean, even if
she was a grandma,

15:22.617 --> 15:24.358
that'd be okay, right?

15:24.488 --> 15:27.361
I mean, my grandma, she's only
30 years older than me.

15:27.491 --> 15:28.666
[ Laughter ]

15:28.797 --> 15:30.842
Okay.
So then you're...

15:30.973 --> 15:32.714
If your mom was...If your mom was...

15:32.844 --> 15:34.498
[ Laughter ]

15:34.629 --> 15:36.718
They were both very young.Oh.

15:36.848 --> 15:38.981
Whatever!
Diane is not a grandma!

15:39.112 --> 15:41.114
She's an aunt who smells
like Herbal Essences

15:41.244 --> 15:42.724
and is very nice to me.

15:42.854 --> 15:45.292
Well, she is
practically my aunt!

15:45.422 --> 15:47.076
It's like you hooked up
with my family!

15:47.207 --> 15:50.079
Well, then, you're related,
almost, huh?

15:50.210 --> 15:51.776
Whatever happened
to loyalty, Neil?

15:51.907 --> 15:54.127
Gee, Kev, I don't know.
Maybe it went out the window

15:54.257 --> 15:56.912
when you ditched me
and I got arrested alone!

15:57.043 --> 15:59.088
Neil,
you misunderstand.

15:59.219 --> 16:01.873
I'm talking about
your loyalty to me,

16:02.004 --> 16:03.310
not the other way
around.

16:03.440 --> 16:05.138
You know what, man?
I'm done.

16:05.268 --> 16:08.576
You've been a jerk to me for --
for -- for -- forever, I think.

16:08.706 --> 16:09.969
Oh, yeah?
Name one time.

16:10.099 --> 16:12.928
The time you ditched me
and I got arrested!

16:13.059 --> 16:14.712
That's real mature,
Neil.

16:14.843 --> 16:16.845
About as mature
as your new girlfriend.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.107
[Chuckles]

16:18.238 --> 16:19.761
No.

16:19.891 --> 16:21.328
[ Laughter ]

16:21.458 --> 16:23.373
Goodbye, Kevi.
It's time for you to go.

16:23.504 --> 16:25.419
Fine. Whatever.

16:25.549 --> 16:27.595
I got my own
smoking-hot girlfriend

16:27.725 --> 16:28.857
to take care of me,
so...

16:28.988 --> 16:30.728
Oh, no, I-I didn't
even shower today.

16:30.859 --> 16:32.730
Babe, how about
you don't announce it

16:32.861 --> 16:34.994
to the whole bar
when you don't shower?

16:35.124 --> 16:37.257
[ Laughter ]

16:37.387 --> 16:45.439
♪

16:45.917 --> 16:47.267
[Breathing sharply]

16:47.397 --> 16:53.534
♪

16:53.664 --> 16:59.801
♪

16:59.931 --> 17:02.151
[Keys jingle, lock clicks]

17:02.282 --> 17:09.941
♪

17:10.071 --> 17:17.339
♪

17:17.471 --> 17:21.040
[Grunts]

17:21.170 --> 17:22.780
[Knock on door]

17:22.911 --> 17:25.218
[Thunder rumbles]

17:25.348 --> 17:29.700
♪

17:29.831 --> 17:31.833
Hi, Allison.

17:34.183 --> 17:35.750
Hi.

17:39.667 --> 17:41.799
[Thunder rumbling]

17:45.151 --> 17:48.023
You did this to get me
to stop asking questions?

17:48.154 --> 17:50.460
To give Patty an out?

17:50.591 --> 17:52.462
Patty didn't need an out.

17:52.593 --> 17:55.117
I deserve the blame.

17:55.248 --> 17:58.642
And she knows you're alive,
I'm assuming.

17:58.773 --> 18:02.124
Yeah. I --
Yeah, I think so.

18:02.255 --> 18:06.215
[Sighs] This explains why
she won't leave Worcester.

18:06.346 --> 18:08.261
Like one of those
captain's widows,

18:08.391 --> 18:10.350
waiting for him
to come back.

18:10.480 --> 18:14.658
You're surprised that Patty
doesn't want to leave Worcester?

18:14.789 --> 18:16.704
I don't think
you can put that one me.

18:16.834 --> 18:20.403
Right. But there's plenty
that I can.

18:20.534 --> 18:23.145
For the last year, since
Wyndorff broke into your house,

18:23.276 --> 18:26.366
I feel like everything's
been a little...off,

18:26.496 --> 18:29.543
like a fraction of an inch,
and I just can't move on.

18:29.673 --> 18:33.068
So I'm just gonna say
what I think happened out loud,

18:33.199 --> 18:36.158
and we'll take it
from there.

18:36.289 --> 18:39.727
You faked your own death.
That's obvious.

18:39.857 --> 18:41.642
But before that,
you and Patty

18:41.772 --> 18:44.297
assaulted a trucker
in Vermont for his pills.

18:44.427 --> 18:46.690
Those pills and cash
were given to Nick Wyndorff

18:46.821 --> 18:49.824
in exchange to
break into your house.

18:49.954 --> 18:52.305
And that's where
I lose the thread.

18:52.435 --> 18:54.176
♪

18:54.307 --> 18:57.310
Or really where I want
to drop the thread.

18:57.440 --> 18:58.659
[Thunder rumbles]

18:58.789 --> 19:03.272
♪

19:03.403 --> 19:04.882
Right.

19:05.013 --> 19:08.973
♪

19:09.104 --> 19:12.455
That was you, uh,
following me in the Jeep?

19:12.586 --> 19:15.545
♪

19:15.676 --> 19:18.983
I had a friend up here
looking for you.

19:19.114 --> 19:22.987
I must say, you're
really great at running.

19:23.118 --> 19:26.469
Well, not good enough,
apparently.

19:26.600 --> 19:28.558
♪

19:28.689 --> 19:31.126
Is the rest of
the Worcester PD out there?

19:33.172 --> 19:34.738
It's just me.

19:36.392 --> 19:37.872
Why?

19:39.526 --> 19:40.744
Because I don't think

19:40.875 --> 19:44.792
it will do anyone any good
to tell them.

19:44.922 --> 19:46.924
I think
Kevin might disagree.

19:47.055 --> 19:50.145
I'm not really concerned
with protecting Kevin.

19:50.276 --> 19:52.278
Or anyone like him,
really.

19:52.408 --> 19:55.150
That's been my job
for years, so...

19:57.283 --> 19:59.285
But...

19:59.415 --> 20:00.764
[Sighs]

20:00.895 --> 20:03.158
Nick Wyndorff died
last week.

20:05.639 --> 20:08.946
And as far as I'm concerned,
this died with him.

20:09.077 --> 20:10.992
Ohh.

20:13.647 --> 20:15.170
Thank you.

20:15.301 --> 20:17.651
I'm not doing this
to be nice.

20:17.781 --> 20:20.741
I'm doing this because
I don't think you're the enemy.

20:20.871 --> 20:23.483
♪

20:23.613 --> 20:26.007
You, either.

20:26.137 --> 20:27.487
But that's about it.

20:27.617 --> 20:32.970
♪

20:33.101 --> 20:38.324
♪

20:38.454 --> 20:39.803
Hey.

20:41.805 --> 20:43.416
Good luck, Allison.

20:43.546 --> 20:49.204
♪

20:49.335 --> 20:51.424
[Door closes][Exhales sharply]

20:51.554 --> 20:58.648
♪

20:58.779 --> 21:00.911
[Indistinct conversations]

21:01.042 --> 21:03.262
[Thunder rumbling]

21:07.266 --> 21:10.704
Laura: [Chuckles]
You seem like you hate that.

21:10.834 --> 21:12.009
I kinda do.

21:12.140 --> 21:13.750
Did they give you
the wrong thing?

21:13.881 --> 21:15.622
Nope.

21:16.927 --> 21:19.582
Are you okay?Yeah, I'm just homesick.

21:19.713 --> 21:23.064
Where'd you say
you were from again?

21:23.194 --> 21:25.066
Uh, I didn't. Uh...

21:26.981 --> 21:28.983
I'm from Worcester.

21:30.376 --> 21:31.768
Oh.

21:31.899 --> 21:33.814
You need money for a train
or something? [Chuckles]

21:33.944 --> 21:35.468
No, I don't need money.

21:35.598 --> 21:39.254
Well, why can't you
go back?

21:39.385 --> 21:40.908
I can.

21:42.388 --> 21:46.261
But, also, I can't.
I, uh -- I don't deserve it.

21:46.392 --> 21:48.829
You don't deserve...
Worcester?

21:48.959 --> 21:51.222
♪

21:51.353 --> 21:54.617
Mm. I'm just not
a good person.

21:54.748 --> 21:56.140
Sure you are!

21:56.271 --> 21:58.099
Well, now's the time
you tell me

21:58.229 --> 22:00.971
that everyone has
some good in them?

22:01.102 --> 22:02.930
Fuck no.

22:05.324 --> 22:07.108
I mean, you think I loan out
my asshole brother

22:07.238 --> 22:09.502
to be just
anyone's handyman?

22:09.632 --> 22:16.422
♪

22:16.552 --> 22:23.472
♪

22:23.603 --> 22:30.740
♪

22:30.871 --> 22:33.526
[Door opens and closes]

22:35.266 --> 22:37.225
Oh. Hey.

22:40.663 --> 22:42.622
Hello.

22:42.752 --> 22:45.233
I just quit.

22:45.364 --> 22:47.975
You quit?

22:48.105 --> 22:50.064
Like, your job?
Yes.

22:52.022 --> 22:54.677
Just like that?Well, not just like that.

22:54.808 --> 22:57.027
I've been miserable for a while.
You know that.

22:57.158 --> 23:01.771
Yeah, Tam, but isn't that
just sort of life for everybody?

23:01.902 --> 23:03.947
Not me.
I'm not staying stuck

23:04.078 --> 23:05.732
in things that are
not working anymore.

23:05.862 --> 23:08.561
I wanted options,
and now I have them.

23:08.691 --> 23:10.563
Oh.

23:12.782 --> 23:16.133
This is the part where you tell
me again that we should move.

23:16.264 --> 23:18.745
Patty, you know we need
to get out of Worcester.

23:18.875 --> 23:22.531
No. No, I don't.

23:22.662 --> 23:25.404
What is so wrong with
staying where you grew up?

23:25.534 --> 23:27.144
Why should I want to leave?

23:27.275 --> 23:29.233
Because this place
is haunted.

23:29.364 --> 23:33.412
Everywhere I look, I see
somewhere you lied to me.

23:33.542 --> 23:35.936
I know I messed up.

23:36.066 --> 23:38.939
And I'm sorry.

23:39.069 --> 23:41.724
But are we ever gonna be able
to just move past it?

23:41.855 --> 23:45.119
Maybe, but not here,
where everything happened.

23:48.296 --> 23:51.430
I need something
to change.

23:51.560 --> 23:54.128
I understand,
and I want you to be happy.

23:57.087 --> 24:00.569
But I can't uproot my life
just to make you happy.

24:04.660 --> 24:06.227
Okay, Patty.

24:08.142 --> 24:10.013
What do you want?

24:11.841 --> 24:13.582
I'm sorry.

24:16.237 --> 24:17.586
But not this.

24:17.717 --> 24:22.939
♪

24:23.070 --> 24:28.249
♪

24:32.296 --> 24:37.606
♪

24:37.737 --> 24:43.264
♪

24:45.614 --> 24:47.790
I need you to talk
to Diane for me.

24:47.921 --> 24:49.270
Excuse me?

24:49.400 --> 24:51.707
She's all pissed because
I didn't propose

24:51.838 --> 24:54.014
or whatever after Kevin found us
making out upstairs.

24:54.144 --> 24:55.668
What do you want me
to do about it?

24:55.798 --> 24:58.932
Tell her I've been off lately
'cause you messed me up.

24:59.062 --> 25:01.630
Tell her Dad used to hit us,
and she should feel bad for me.

25:01.761 --> 25:03.763
I don't know.
Make something up.

25:07.070 --> 25:08.594
You have to leave.

25:08.724 --> 25:10.465
Not 'til you say
you're gonna talk to Diane.

25:10.596 --> 25:14.513
No, I mean you have to
move out, for both of us.

25:14.643 --> 25:15.775
You can't make me.

25:15.905 --> 25:17.516
Yeah, I can.

25:17.646 --> 25:20.823
I should've done it years ago,
and I'm doing it now.

25:20.954 --> 25:24.261
You're not just gonna
throw me out on the street

25:24.392 --> 25:27.090
because I asked you
to do one thing.

25:28.744 --> 25:31.617
One thing?

25:31.747 --> 25:32.922
One thing?!

25:33.053 --> 25:34.750
Jesus. Calm down.

25:34.881 --> 25:37.144
You spent the last 30 years
asking me to do

25:37.274 --> 25:39.886
one thing after another,
and I've done them!

25:40.016 --> 25:41.931
But I don't remember
you ever asking me

25:42.062 --> 25:45.282
what it is that I want!

25:45.413 --> 25:47.589
Fine.
What do you want?

25:50.505 --> 25:52.638
I want to sit out there
and smoke

25:52.768 --> 25:55.684
and not worry about
what anybody else needs.

25:55.815 --> 25:57.251
[Scoffs]

25:57.381 --> 26:00.167
That's the one thing
I haven't been doing for you?

26:00.297 --> 26:02.430
Jesus.
That's pathetic.

26:02.561 --> 26:05.651
It's the most
I could come up with.

26:05.781 --> 26:08.741
Maybe if I could do that, I
could figure something else out.

26:08.871 --> 26:12.092
♪

26:12.222 --> 26:15.835
But as long as you're here,
even that's impossible.

26:15.965 --> 26:18.751
♪

26:18.881 --> 26:21.275
Where am I supposed to go?

26:21.405 --> 26:24.887
You're 36 years old, Neil.

26:25.018 --> 26:27.368
Don't you think it's time
you figured that out without me?

26:29.675 --> 26:31.111
[Exhales sharply]

26:31.241 --> 26:38.901
♪

26:39.032 --> 26:46.779
♪

26:46.909 --> 26:54.264
♪

26:54.395 --> 26:57.790
Jesse, could you put on
some more decaf? Jesus Christ.

26:59.139 --> 27:01.010
I-I did some back
from the dead,

27:01.141 --> 27:04.623
so you're not
entirely wrong.

27:04.753 --> 27:07.495
Sorry. I'm not serious.
I know I'm not Jesus Christ.

27:10.411 --> 27:12.326
[Both laugh]

27:14.589 --> 27:18.637
I really thought
I'd never see you again.

27:18.767 --> 27:20.073
Thought or hoped?

27:20.203 --> 27:21.509
Uh, no. Not hoped.

27:21.640 --> 27:23.816
I'm glad I was wrong.

27:25.121 --> 27:27.950
I really thought it was
the right thing to do.

27:28.081 --> 27:30.649
Well, but you know we're
not actually better off

27:30.779 --> 27:32.433
without you, right?

27:34.565 --> 27:36.176
Trying to believe that.

27:36.306 --> 27:39.832
Well, Patty really does know
you
better than I do.

27:39.962 --> 27:43.618
And, um...
how is Patty?

27:43.749 --> 27:45.794
I think she'll really
want to see you again.

27:45.925 --> 27:47.709
Yeah. Yeah.
Not yet.

27:47.840 --> 27:52.540
I-I still have a few things
I need to figure out first.

27:52.671 --> 27:53.933
Yeah. Wait.

27:54.063 --> 27:56.457
So, how are you gonna
explain to everyone

27:56.587 --> 27:59.068
that you're back here,
alive?

27:59.199 --> 28:01.244
Kevin basically
buried you.

28:01.375 --> 28:05.466
He made a really big deal
about it. People know.

28:05.596 --> 28:08.643
Those are the things
I need to figure out.

28:08.774 --> 28:10.471
What are you gonna say?

28:12.299 --> 28:13.692
That I ran,

28:13.822 --> 28:18.392
that I got away from Kevin
the only way I knew how.

28:20.350 --> 28:22.222
So the truth, I guess.

28:22.352 --> 28:23.963
How's that feel?

28:25.747 --> 28:27.401
New.

28:31.144 --> 28:34.060
So Kevin really made
a big deal when I died?

28:34.190 --> 28:35.626
He grew a beard.

28:35.757 --> 28:37.367
Mnh.
Yeah.

28:37.498 --> 28:41.937
He had this elaborate memorial
service at a bowling alley.

28:42.068 --> 28:43.678
Mm-hmm.
Yeah.

28:43.809 --> 28:46.420
That's where
he met Molly.

28:46.550 --> 28:47.900
Who?

28:48.030 --> 28:49.423
[Groans softly]

28:50.598 --> 28:52.687
Sam, who the fuck
is Molly?

28:52.818 --> 28:54.123
[Bowling pins crashing]

28:54.254 --> 28:56.256
[Spray can hissing]

28:56.386 --> 29:04.003
♪

29:04.133 --> 29:05.744
Thank you.

29:07.746 --> 29:09.008
Hi.

29:13.621 --> 29:14.927
Aren't you...?

29:15.057 --> 29:18.234
Allison McRoberts.
Yeah.

29:18.365 --> 29:20.323
I was gonna say "dead."

29:20.454 --> 29:21.803
Well, about that --

29:21.934 --> 29:25.328
uh, I was hoping
you had a second to talk.

29:25.459 --> 29:27.156
[Bowling pins crash]

29:27.287 --> 29:29.985
[Pounding]Diane!

29:30.116 --> 29:32.335
Diane, come on!

29:32.466 --> 29:35.817
Neil?! What the hell
are you thinking?!

29:35.948 --> 29:39.647
I made a mistake.
I can't just let this go.

29:39.778 --> 29:40.953
I-I think
I'm in love with you.

29:41.083 --> 29:43.520
Oh. Shut up.
Shut up. Come here.

29:43.651 --> 29:45.653
[Dog barking]

29:47.568 --> 29:50.527
You cannot
just show up here.

29:50.658 --> 29:52.486
Do you have any idea
what Chuck would do to you?

29:52.616 --> 29:54.575
To -- To me?That-- That's the thing.

29:54.705 --> 29:57.056
I don't care.
I don't care who knows.

29:57.186 --> 29:59.145
Not --
Not Chuck, not Kevin.Well, that must be nice,

29:59.275 --> 30:01.234
'cause I had to pay
Kevin 500 bucks

30:01.364 --> 30:04.715
to not "let it slip"
at bowling last night.

30:04.846 --> 30:06.369
I care if Chuck knows.

30:06.500 --> 30:10.156
Why?
He's a dick to you.

30:10.286 --> 30:11.766
Are you drunk?

30:11.897 --> 30:15.770
Diane, I need you.
When -- When we're together,

30:15.901 --> 30:18.251
I feel...a lot.

30:18.381 --> 30:20.731
And mostly, it's good.

30:20.862 --> 30:23.038
We could --
We could leave together.

30:23.169 --> 30:26.172
We could leave together.Who says I want to leave?

30:26.302 --> 30:28.391
I mean,
I-I tried that once.

30:28.522 --> 30:29.958
It -- It was -- It was --

30:30.089 --> 30:32.656
[Sighs]

30:32.787 --> 30:36.835
I-It's possible.
It's possible. Maybe.

30:36.965 --> 30:40.403
But --
But not with you like this.

30:40.534 --> 30:43.972
I haven't had a drink
for 212 days,

30:44.103 --> 30:48.672
and if I was gonna go somewhere
and start over again,

30:48.803 --> 30:51.240
stuff would
have to be different.

30:51.371 --> 30:52.763
I can be better.

30:52.894 --> 30:56.115
You -- You can
make me better.

30:58.204 --> 31:00.249
That's not my job, Neil.

31:01.903 --> 31:05.646
You figure it out.
And maybe.

31:05.776 --> 31:08.040
But I can't do it
for you.

31:08.170 --> 31:16.048
♪

31:16.178 --> 31:18.137
[Dog barking]

31:18.267 --> 31:20.182
[Sighs]

31:20.313 --> 31:28.060
♪

31:31.106 --> 31:32.891
It's quiet in here.[Chair squeaks]

31:33.021 --> 31:34.283
[ Laughter ]

31:34.414 --> 31:37.286
A little too quiet.

31:37.417 --> 31:39.680
So quiet
that if I stop talking,

31:39.810 --> 31:41.900
it'll be complete silence,
which I cannot handle,

31:42.030 --> 31:45.338
so I am just gonna say words
that I think sound cool.

31:45.468 --> 31:47.383
[ Laughter ]

31:47.514 --> 31:49.516
Swashbuckler.

31:50.038 --> 31:51.300
Noodle.

31:51.431 --> 31:53.433
Spelunking.
Hey.

31:53.563 --> 31:56.044
Quadru-- Oh.
Oh! Hey.

31:56.175 --> 31:57.480
[Exhales deeply]
I'm so glad you're here.

31:57.611 --> 31:59.743
Really?
Yeah. Of course.

31:59.874 --> 32:01.484
Um, it's just last time
I stopped by

32:01.615 --> 32:02.790
without calling first,

32:02.921 --> 32:05.488
you called me
a "stage five clinger."

32:05.619 --> 32:06.707
[ Laughter ]
I did not!

32:06.837 --> 32:08.709
Yes, you did,
because then I said,

32:08.839 --> 32:11.103
"Oh, do we still quote
'Wedding Crashers'?"

32:11.233 --> 32:13.757
And you said, "I'll stop quoting
'Wedding Crashers'

32:13.888 --> 32:15.890
when they pry it
from my cold, dead hands."

32:16.021 --> 32:18.110
And then I said,
"What -- Who's 'they'?

32:18.240 --> 32:19.807
What are 'they' prying?"

32:19.938 --> 32:21.504
And then you said,
"It's a figure of speech.

32:21.635 --> 32:23.115
It's probably
Shakespeare."

32:23.245 --> 32:25.073
And then I said --
Whoa, whoa.

32:25.204 --> 32:26.466
Whoa, whoa.

32:26.596 --> 32:28.033
Where was this memory

32:28.163 --> 32:30.426
when you were ordering pizza
over the phone?

32:30.557 --> 32:31.601
What?

32:32.254 --> 32:34.778
Sorry.
That was the other one.

32:34.909 --> 32:38.391
But if I did say that,
it was just a joke.

32:38.521 --> 32:40.132
Oh. Yeah.

32:40.262 --> 32:41.960
Well, four months
together,

32:42.090 --> 32:43.700
still never knowing
when you're serious.

32:43.831 --> 32:45.311
Rule of thumb --

32:45.441 --> 32:49.315
If you're offended by
what I said, I was just joking.

32:49.445 --> 32:51.056
But don't worry.

32:51.186 --> 32:52.927
You're gonna have plenty of time
to figure this stuff out,

32:53.058 --> 32:56.191
because --
big exciting news --

32:56.322 --> 32:57.192
you're moving in!

32:57.323 --> 32:58.498
[ Laughter ]

32:58.628 --> 32:59.542
I'm moving in?

32:59.673 --> 33:01.153
I know.
I'm a catch.

33:01.283 --> 33:02.763
It's okay to get
a little excited.

33:02.893 --> 33:04.634
Kevin, t-this is --

33:04.765 --> 33:08.551
We...We --
We are moving very fast.

33:08.682 --> 33:10.336
Lovebug...
[Chuckles]

33:10.466 --> 33:13.426
...when do you think we can
start, uh, moving your stuff in?

33:13.556 --> 33:14.427
You know, get going?

33:14.557 --> 33:16.559
[ Laughter ]

33:16.690 --> 33:18.822
Kinda backing up there,
huh?

33:18.953 --> 33:21.173
No. No. It's just --
just 'cause I'm gonna go.

33:21.303 --> 33:22.609
I'm gonna, uh...
What?

33:22.739 --> 33:24.611
I gotta go --
I gotta go get some cigarettes.

33:24.741 --> 33:26.787
Oh. Okay. Phew!
I thought you were leaving.

33:26.917 --> 33:28.484
Oh!
[Laughs]

33:28.615 --> 33:30.182
[Laughing]
No.

33:30.312 --> 33:31.879
No!

33:32.010 --> 33:34.142
[Laughing]

33:34.273 --> 33:36.405
[Laughs]

33:36.536 --> 33:38.712
[ Laughter ]

33:40.105 --> 33:43.456
But wait.
She doesn't smoke cigarettes.

33:43.586 --> 33:46.024
[ Laughter ]

33:50.593 --> 33:52.204
What the hell is with everyone?

33:52.334 --> 33:54.989
Allison: Bad day?
Oh, my God!

33:55.120 --> 33:56.338
[ Laughter ]

33:56.469 --> 33:58.427
This is some sort
of horrible nightmare!

33:59.515 --> 34:03.345
Or it's some sort
of wonderful dream!

34:03.476 --> 34:06.000
Oh!
Allison, you're alive!

34:06.131 --> 34:07.654
This is amazing!

34:07.784 --> 34:09.090
And you have
great timing, too,

34:09.221 --> 34:10.831
because I'm pretty sure
I just got dumped.

